        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer73587190" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17849033738449375557">I read this before, but lately, I got a yearning to read it again, and I&apos;m so glad I did. Rawlings lyrical descriptions are so beautifully crafted. The word magic is strong in this book, making me wish I could cut out sentences to adorn my walls. So poignant. I think I&apos;m enjoying it even more this time than the first time I read it, as I&apos;m coming to it older and having experienced more disappointments myself. <br/><br/>I was originally drawn to this book by the tattered jacket with the beautiful illustrat</span>
  <span id="freeText17849033738449375557" style="display:none">I read this before, but lately, I got a yearning to read it again, and I'm so glad I did. Rawlings lyrical descriptions are so beautifully crafted. The word magic is strong in this book, making me wish I could cut out sentences to adorn my walls. So poignant. I think I'm enjoying it even more this time than the first time I read it, as I'm coming to it older and having experienced more disappointments myself. <br /><br />I was originally drawn to this book by the tattered jacket with the beautiful illustration of Ase standing against the night sky. It is such a perfect illustration of the feel of this book, the solitary man, nature, strength, and pathos. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17849033738449375557" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

