<span id="freeTextContainer1178337687065966981">Though Rawlings can write well, I am certain, the plot of this book was a snooze fest. I am not kidding. I have been reading this book, a couple pages at a time for almost a year. I can generally crack out a 300 page fiction book in a day or day and a half. A week at most if I have no time to read. This book was just uninspiring and I never did start to enjoy it. Asa, as a character, was easy to despise even though you are supposed to sympathize with him. That made the book challenging.<br/><br/>For a ful</span>
  <span id="freeText1178337687065966981" style="display:none">Though Rawlings can write well, I am certain, the plot of this book was a snooze fest. I am not kidding. I have been reading this book, a couple pages at a time for almost a year. I can generally crack out a 300 page fiction book in a day or day and a half. A week at most if I have no time to read. This book was just uninspiring and I never did start to enjoy it. Asa, as a character, was easy to despise even though you are supposed to sympathize with him. That made the book challenging.<br /><br />For a full review visit <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://ireadalotofbooks.com/the-sojourner-by-marjorie-kinnan-rawlings/">http://ireadalotofbooks.com/the-sojou...</a></span>
