<span id="freeTextContainer7065578899069025171">We were fortunate in that we had a lot of books to read from our home library and this was one of them. I probably read this when I was about 16 and have now reread it 53 years later. Although I did not remember anything about the book, I did remember that I loved it. I was not disappointed on this second read so many years later. What a beautifully written book. I believe some books are made to be read aloud and this would be one. The descriptions are so beautiful they tend to be poetic at time</span>
  <span id="freeText7065578899069025171" style="display:none">We were fortunate in that we had a lot of books to read from our home library and this was one of them. I probably read this when I was about 16 and have now reread it 53 years later. Although I did not remember anything about the book, I did remember that I loved it. I was not disappointed on this second read so many years later. What a beautifully written book. I believe some books are made to be read aloud and this would be one. The descriptions are so beautiful they tend to be poetic at times. You will feel so many emotions through out this book but Ase, the main character, will hold your respect and love in each page. I read that the author, Margaret Rawlings died shortly after finishing this book. I will once again remember how beautiful this book is even as I forget details.</span>
