<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer9321893669612962564">Marjorie Kinnan Rawlings was an American author who lived in rural Florida and wrote novels with rural themes and settings. Her best known work, The Yearling, about a boy who adopts an orphaned fawn, won a Pulitzer Prize for fiction in 1939 and was later made into a movie of the same title, <i>The Yearling</i>. The book was written long before the concept of young-adult fiction, but is now commonly inclu</span>
  <span id="freeText9321893669612962564" style="display:none">Marjorie Kinnan Rawlings was an American author who lived in rural Florida and wrote novels with rural themes and settings. Her best known work, The Yearling, about a boy who adopts an orphaned fawn, won a Pulitzer Prize for fiction in 1939 and was later made into a movie of the same title, <i>The Yearling</i>. The book was written long before the concept of young-adult fiction, but is now commonly included in teen-reading lists.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9321893669612962564" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

